---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Terms of Service | Smesh.Dev" 
  description="Terms of Service for Smesh.dev. Review our consulting, custom n8n automation, and web engineering terms under BismillahTC Digital Services."
>
  <section class="site-shell py-16 md:py-24 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <span class="section-kicker">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="display-title text-[color:var(--ink)] text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight font-display border-b border-slate-200 pb-6">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 font-sans">
        Last Updated: June 2026 &mdash; Khanewal, Pakistan
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 space-y-10 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-655 font-sans font-light">
      <p>
        Welcome to <strong>Smesh.dev</strong>. These Terms of Service govern your use of our website, digital resources, and custom software consulting services. Smesh.dev is the personal automation studio of lead systems engineer <strong>Haider Ali</strong>, operating under <strong>BismillahTC Digital Services</strong> based in Khanewal, Punjab, Pakistan.
      </p>

      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">1. Services & Project Scope</h2>
        <p>
          We provide custom development services including n8n workflow integration, Supabase databases, AI support chatbots, offline-first POS sync configurations, and Astro/Next.js business websites.
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Free Audits:</strong> Our free technical consultations are educational. They do not constitute a contract or guarantee of system build deliverables.</li>
          <li><strong>Project Agreements:</strong> The exact deliverables, scope of work, timeline, and final specifications for any paid consulting will be detailed in a separate written project proposal signed by both parties.</li>
          <li><strong>Scope Changes:</strong> Any adjustments, additions, or modifications to the agreed deliverables after project kickoff will be treated as a scope change and may affect project timelines and pricing.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">2. Client Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>
          To ensure successful project delivery within estimated timelines, you agree to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li>Provide necessary access credentials (e.g. database keys, hosting tokens, API credentials) in a timely manner.</li>
          <li>Respond to layout reviews, system validation requests, and approvals within 3 business days.</li>
          <li>Pay all third-party hosting fees (Vercel, Supabase, n8n Cloud) and API usage costs (OpenAI, WhatsApp Business API) directly.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">3. Pricing & Payment Terms</h2>
        <p>
          All pricing quotes are project-based and paid in flat rates as detailed in your project proposal:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Deposits:</strong> A kickoff deposit (typically 30% to 50% of the project total) is required before we begin any database configuration or coding.</li>
          <li><strong>Milestones:</strong> Remaining payments are due upon completion of specific project deliverables.</li>
          <li><strong>Handovers:</strong> Final code transfer, live deployment connection, and master credentials will be handed over only after the final invoice is paid in full.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">4. Intellectual Property & Ownership</h2>
        <p>
          We believe in direct developer handovers without vendor lock-in:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Your Ownership:</strong> Upon final payment of the project total, you receive 100% intellectual property ownership of all custom-built web code, custom database schemas, and tailored n8n workflow scripts.</li>
          <li><strong>Pre-existing Code:</strong> Smesh.dev retains ownership of our pre-existing starter boilerplates, generic helper utilities, and abstract database design patterns. You receive a perpetual, royalty-free license to use these embedded items in your project.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 5 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">5. Confidentiality</h2>
        <p>
          We respect your business operations. Smesh.dev commits to keeping all proprietary trade details, client catalogs, private database inputs, and communication histories strictly confidential. We will never share your login credentials or private data keys with third parties.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 6 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, Smesh.dev and BismillahTC Digital Services will not be liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages (including loss of sales, profits, or database logs). Our total liability for any claim arising from a project is strictly capped at the total amount paid by you for that specific engagement. We are not responsible for outages caused by third-party hosting platforms (Vercel, Supabase) or external API changes (OpenAI, Meta APIs).
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 7 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">7. Project Termination</h2>
        <p>
          Either party may terminate a project agreement with 7 days written notice. In the event of termination, you will be invoiced for all development hours and completed milestones delivered up to the termination date. All completed custom code and configurations paid for will be handed over post-payment.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 8 -->
      <div class="space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">8. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms of Service and any custom project agreements are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the Islamic Republic of Pakistan, subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts in Khanewal, Punjab, Pakistan.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 9 -->
      <div class="space-y-4 border-t border-slate-200 pt-6">
        <h2 class="text-base font-bold text-slate-900 font-display">Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions or require clarification regarding these terms, please contact me directly:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-xs">
          <li><strong>Lead Developer:</strong> Haider Ali</li>
          <li><strong>Entity:</strong> BismillahTC Digital Services</li>
          <li><strong>Address:</strong> Khanewal, Punjab, Pakistan</li>
          <li><strong>Direct Email:</strong> <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`} class="text-[color:var(--accent-strong)] font-semibold underline">{site.email}</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
